<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4565145>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Clastoptera querci photomicrographs. a) Dorsal habitus. b) Lateral habitus. c) Ventral habitus. d) Close-up of pronotum and vertex, arrows point to diagnostic reddish marks. e) Dark color form. f) Left to right, nymphal instars 1 to 5, ventral view. g) Male genital capsule, ventral view. h) Female, left second valvula. i) Male genitalia close-up, ventral view. Figures 2a, b, d from holotype; 2e, g, h, i from paratypes. Scale bars for a–f = 1.0 mm, for g–i = 0.1 mm. Photograph 2c by Tony Dickens, FDACS/DPI." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4565145/files/figure.png" .

